1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:01:05,000
Watch on kisskh.me

2
00:01:26,620 --> 00:01:29,970
[Moonlight]

3
00:01:30,140 --> 00:01:33,000
[Episode 10]
Watch on kisskh.me

4
00:01:33,030 --> 00:01:35,590
Being a commercial writer isn't that bad.

5
00:01:35,590 --> 00:01:37,190
Without a slight desire

6
00:01:37,190 --> 00:01:38,190
to write,

7
00:01:38,190 --> 00:01:40,310
you can't write anything popular at all.

8
00:01:40,310 --> 00:01:41,550
Besides, I've read it.

9
00:01:41,550 --> 00:01:43,990
You really poured your heart
into this book.

10
00:01:49,300 --> 00:01:50,300
Listen.

11
00:01:50,300 --> 00:01:52,870
Don't be fooled by Mr Zhou Chuan

12
00:01:52,870 --> 00:01:55,070
and think he is above you.

13
00:01:55,790 --> 00:01:56,750
That fellow

14
00:01:56,750 --> 00:01:58,990
is only good at twisting words.

15
00:01:58,990 --> 00:01:59,950
You'd better not

16
00:01:59,950 --> 00:02:01,740
talk to him about life
or ambition whatsoever.

17
00:02:01,740 --> 00:02:02,940
He's toxic.

18
00:02:05,190 --> 00:02:06,950
I really want to record all these

19
00:02:06,950 --> 00:02:08,070
and send it to Zhou Chuan.

20
00:02:09,030 --> 00:02:10,310
Oh, don't.

21
00:02:10,630 --> 00:02:12,910
Let's just continue eating, Mr Jiang.

22
00:02:29,579 --> 00:02:31,780
Why isn't she back yet?

23
00:02:34,200 --> 00:02:36,450
[Corner Bookstore]

24
00:02:42,829 --> 00:02:44,060
[Hi, we have received your submission
under science fiction genre.]

25
00:02:44,060 --> 00:02:45,380
[But it's far from what we imagined.
Hope we can collaborate in the next one.]

26
00:02:52,190 --> 00:02:52,950
Here's your coffee.

27
00:02:53,270 --> 00:02:54,220
Thanks.

28
00:02:54,270 --> 00:02:57,300
[The Long Goodbye]

29
00:02:57,660 --> 00:02:58,580
[The Long Goodbye]

30
00:03:07,100 --> 00:03:08,670
[You like this book too?]

31
00:03:10,990 --> 00:03:11,710
[Yes, I do.]

32
00:03:12,670 --> 00:03:13,550
[Why?]

33
00:03:15,900 --> 00:03:18,070
[It's supposed to be a detective fiction]

34
00:03:18,070 --> 00:03:20,110
[but my mind is not only on the mystery.]

35
00:03:20,110 --> 00:03:21,710
[I'm more intrigued]

36
00:03:22,150 --> 00:03:23,380
[by the characters]

37
00:03:23,380 --> 00:03:25,310
[and how they cross paths.]

38
00:03:26,110 --> 00:03:28,030
[It's exactly Raymond's charm.]

39
00:03:28,630 --> 00:03:30,030
[I like this book too.]

40
00:03:30,420 --> 00:03:31,870
[Every character]

41
00:03:31,870 --> 00:03:33,630
[has his or her own story.]

42
00:03:34,190 --> 00:03:35,550
[Moreover his writing]

43
00:03:35,550 --> 00:03:36,670
[is known for one unique feature.]

44
00:03:36,670 --> 00:03:38,710
[He uses simple]

45
00:03:38,710 --> 00:03:39,910
[but very precise words]

46
00:03:39,910 --> 00:03:40,980
[to illustrate]

47
00:03:40,980 --> 00:03:42,510
[the deepest thoughts of his characters.]

48
00:03:42,910 --> 00:03:43,950
[Very intense.]

49
00:03:44,710 --> 00:03:45,550
[How I wish]

50
00:03:45,550 --> 00:03:47,190
[my novels are as good as his.]

51
00:03:48,350 --> 00:03:49,390
[You're a writer?]

52
00:03:49,390 --> 00:03:50,030
[Yes.]

53
00:03:50,030 --> 00:03:51,950
[I write mostly]

54
00:03:51,950 --> 00:03:53,230
[detective mysteries.]

55
00:03:53,630 --> 00:03:55,150
[I'm an editor.]

56
00:03:55,150 --> 00:03:56,030
[Really?]

57
00:03:56,500 --> 00:03:57,380
[Yes.]

58
00:03:58,700 --> 00:04:00,190
[If you don't mind,]

59
00:04:00,190 --> 00:04:01,830
[I can look at your novel.]

60
00:04:02,790 --> 00:04:03,470
[Sure.]

61
00:04:05,270 --> 00:04:06,310
[I'm Jiang Yu Cheng.]

62
00:04:07,190 --> 00:04:07,790
[I'm Gu Bai Zhi.]

63
00:04:15,790 --> 00:04:17,750
Can I help you?

64
00:04:19,550 --> 00:04:20,430
No, it's fine.

65
00:04:43,510 --> 00:04:46,030
[I bought these couple watches
when I got married.]

66
00:04:46,470 --> 00:04:48,310
[I'm thinking of saving them]

67
00:04:48,310 --> 00:04:51,500
[as a wedding gift to you and Xiao Jiang.]

68
00:04:52,060 --> 00:04:53,909
[No, Ms Liu.]

69
00:04:54,470 --> 00:04:56,190
[Mr Lin left them for you.]

70
00:04:57,910 --> 00:04:59,670
[I'll be seeing him soon.]

71
00:04:59,670 --> 00:05:01,830
[Why do I need these?]

72
00:05:02,710 --> 00:05:06,430
[My only hope is that
you and Xiao Jiang are together.]

73
00:05:06,750 --> 00:05:10,150
[I can then leave in peace.]

74
00:05:10,910 --> 00:05:12,870
[What are you talking about?]

75
00:05:32,310 --> 00:05:34,250
[Gu Bai Zhi]

76
00:05:41,670 --> 00:05:42,470
Hello?

77
00:05:47,500 --> 00:05:48,310
Hello?

78
00:06:05,510 --> 00:06:06,590
Hello?

79
00:06:10,750 --> 00:06:11,630
Just two hours later

80
00:06:11,630 --> 00:06:12,990
and you got yourself this drunk?

81
00:06:12,990 --> 00:06:13,870
Sis.

82
00:06:38,270 --> 00:06:39,190
What is it?

83
00:06:39,190 --> 00:06:41,230
Jiang Yu Cheng.
Why didn't you pick up?

84
00:06:41,990 --> 00:06:42,909
[Are you done?]

85
00:06:42,909 --> 00:06:43,830
[It's just a contract.]

86
00:06:43,830 --> 00:06:44,909
[Can you get it over with?]

87
00:06:45,550 --> 00:06:46,750
I'm starving here.

88
00:06:46,750 --> 00:06:48,900
I haven't eaten anything
after I finished writing.

89
00:06:48,900 --> 00:06:50,830
Can you return my editor to me?

90
00:06:51,870 --> 00:06:53,430
Without Chu Li you'd starve?

91
00:06:55,470 --> 00:06:56,820
If Chu Li doesn't read the manuscript,

92
00:06:56,820 --> 00:06:58,260
I can't eat.

93
00:06:59,550 --> 00:07:00,780
Are you crazy?

94
00:07:00,780 --> 00:07:01,830
You kept her this late.

95
00:07:01,830 --> 00:07:03,070
You're the crazy one here.

96
00:07:03,070 --> 00:07:04,150
Not even a single reply.

97
00:07:04,150 --> 00:07:04,990
What happened?

98
00:07:04,990 --> 00:07:06,350
She left long ago.

99
00:07:06,620 --> 00:07:08,310
If she didn't reply your message,
why don't you call her?

100
00:07:11,110 --> 00:07:11,830
Right.

101
00:07:17,310 --> 00:07:18,940
Er Gou, let's go.

102
00:07:18,940 --> 00:07:20,550
Let's go for a walk.

103
00:07:20,990 --> 00:07:22,150
Go for a walk.

104
00:07:22,150 --> 00:07:23,310
Mr Zhou Chuan.
It's already so late.

105
00:07:23,310 --> 00:07:24,950
You want to walk the dog now?

106
00:07:26,190 --> 00:07:28,060
Who's walking the dog?

107
00:07:28,390 --> 00:07:29,630
Why didn't you reply my messages?

108
00:07:29,630 --> 00:07:30,710
What took you so long?

109
00:07:31,110 --> 00:07:32,310
You've been talking to him
so many times before.

110
00:07:32,310 --> 00:07:33,430
Aren't you done talking already?

111
00:07:34,390 --> 00:07:35,870
You've gotten attached to him?

112
00:07:37,030 --> 00:07:39,830
Mr Zhou Chuan.
What's brewing in that head now?

113
00:07:39,830 --> 00:07:41,260
My phone died.

114
00:07:41,260 --> 00:07:43,430
I was just seeking advice from Mr Jiang

115
00:07:43,430 --> 00:07:44,590
on book publicity

116
00:07:44,590 --> 00:07:46,070
and ways to engage with

117
00:07:46,070 --> 00:07:47,710
physical booksellers.

118
00:07:48,670 --> 00:07:50,350
Why don't you ask me?

119
00:07:50,350 --> 00:07:51,390
You know about these too?

120
00:07:51,390 --> 00:07:52,940
Are you kidding?

121
00:07:53,380 --> 00:07:54,790
Of course I don't.

122
00:07:54,790 --> 00:07:55,550
Forget it.

123
00:07:55,550 --> 00:07:57,510
Let me make you some chrysanthemum tea

124
00:07:57,510 --> 00:07:58,660
to calm you down.

125
00:07:58,870 --> 00:08:00,310
Make tea? I'm starving.

126
00:08:00,310 --> 00:08:01,270
Make me something to eat.

127
00:08:04,380 --> 00:08:06,140
Have you sealed the deal

128
00:08:06,140 --> 00:08:07,510
on Jiang Yu Cheng's new book?

129
00:08:07,510 --> 00:08:09,070
Not yet.

130
00:08:09,470 --> 00:08:11,550
I want to wait

131
00:08:11,550 --> 00:08:13,940
for the birth of your masterpiece.

132
00:08:13,940 --> 00:08:16,830
The printing house is going to
run out of paper very soon.

133
00:08:17,070 --> 00:08:19,270
I didn't know you have a grudge
on the printing house.

134
00:08:22,110 --> 00:08:23,630
Why are you so confident?

135
00:08:24,150 --> 00:08:25,630
What got into you?

136
00:08:52,020 --> 00:08:53,150
[I've walked the dog.]

137
00:08:52,460 --> 00:09:04,170
[Not Drama King, it's Saviour]

138
00:08:53,150 --> 00:08:54,220
[What do I need you for?]

139
00:08:54,510 --> 00:08:55,910
[Why aren't you back yet?]

140
00:08:55,910 --> 00:08:57,390
[Is there so much to talk about?]

141
00:08:57,390 --> 00:08:59,310
[I'm dying of hunger here.]

142
00:08:59,310 --> 00:09:00,430
[From now onwards,]

143
00:09:00,430 --> 00:09:01,630
[every minute you take to reach home]

144
00:09:01,630 --> 00:09:03,510
[is causing you a hundred in rent.]

145
00:09:23,870 --> 00:09:25,390
Mr Zhou Chuan.

146
00:09:26,110 --> 00:09:28,750
Book of Luo He God is going to print.

147
00:09:28,750 --> 00:09:31,190
You must be nervous.

148
00:09:32,750 --> 00:09:34,310
You should be the one feeling nervous.

149
00:09:34,790 --> 00:09:36,750
You went for a jog and
walked the dog at seven,

150
00:09:36,750 --> 00:09:38,310
showered and set your hair at eight.

151
00:09:38,310 --> 00:09:40,190
Now you are here in time
for breakfast with me.

152
00:09:40,190 --> 00:09:42,710
Isn't this a little too much for you?

153
00:09:43,230 --> 00:09:45,070
I remember Mr Jiang say that

154
00:09:45,070 --> 00:09:46,190
once you are nervous,

155
00:09:46,190 --> 00:09:48,270
you'll try to become a normal person.

156
00:09:49,110 --> 00:09:51,100
You should be the one feeling nervous.

157
00:09:51,100 --> 00:09:52,630
If this book failed to sell,

158
00:09:52,630 --> 00:09:53,910
it won't be the end

159
00:09:53,910 --> 00:09:55,590
for Yuan Yue Publishing House and me.

160
00:09:55,590 --> 00:09:57,110
But without a doubt,

161
00:09:57,990 --> 00:10:00,190
you won't be my managing editor anymore.

162
00:10:01,630 --> 00:10:04,350
[This person who gave me
my first contract]

163
00:10:04,350 --> 00:10:06,110
[will turn into]

164
00:10:06,110 --> 00:10:07,310
[a stranger?]

165
00:10:07,910 --> 00:10:08,870
Don't you think

166
00:10:08,870 --> 00:10:10,950
I'm particularly virtuous and classy?

167
00:10:14,390 --> 00:10:14,980
I'm done talking.

168
00:10:14,980 --> 00:10:16,030
I'm going to office now.

169
00:10:17,030 --> 00:10:18,750
Why are you working on a Sunday?

170
00:10:20,190 --> 00:10:21,790
That's all thanks to you.

171
00:10:21,790 --> 00:10:22,780
You are simply

172
00:10:22,780 --> 00:10:24,190
too important to us.

173
00:10:24,190 --> 00:10:25,150
For the coming Sundays,

174
00:10:25,150 --> 00:10:27,740
our entire department is working overtime
just for you.

175
00:10:27,740 --> 00:10:28,390
Goodbye.

176
00:10:36,430 --> 00:10:38,470
Out on weekends?

177
00:10:38,950 --> 00:10:40,500
You think this is a hotel?

178
00:10:47,910 --> 00:10:49,790
Sis, you're up.

179
00:10:49,790 --> 00:10:50,670
Here.

180
00:10:53,950 --> 00:10:55,430
Why are you in my house?

181
00:10:57,190 --> 00:10:58,510
I called you yesterday.

182
00:10:58,510 --> 00:10:59,830
The bartender answered

183
00:10:59,830 --> 00:11:00,950
and told me you were drunk.

184
00:11:01,430 --> 00:11:03,190
I immediately went to get you.

185
00:11:05,670 --> 00:11:07,870
I'm sorry. Thanks.

186
00:11:07,870 --> 00:11:09,150
Do you still have a headache?

187
00:11:10,950 --> 00:11:11,990
Take this pill.

188
00:11:28,090 --> 00:11:32,930
[Jiang Yu Cheng]

189
00:11:33,280 --> 00:11:36,800
[Jiang Yu Cheng]

190
00:11:42,070 --> 00:11:43,660
Did I say anything last night

191
00:11:43,660 --> 00:11:44,910
that I'm not supposed to?

192
00:11:48,330 --> 00:11:54,400
[Reading Club]

193
00:12:00,520 --> 00:12:03,420
[Reading. The City Never Sleeps]

194
00:12:23,260 --> 00:12:24,550
You're early.

195
00:12:24,750 --> 00:12:26,030
Don't tell me you're here to buy books.

196
00:12:26,710 --> 00:12:28,510
I called you last night.

197
00:12:32,990 --> 00:12:34,670
But when I answered,

198
00:12:35,140 --> 00:12:36,550
you didn't say anything.

199
00:12:37,020 --> 00:12:38,340
I guess you must have called by accident.

200
00:12:45,870 --> 00:12:46,870
Is there anything else?

201
00:12:48,590 --> 00:12:50,270
I visited Ms Liu.

202
00:12:50,270 --> 00:12:52,350
Her condition isn't too good.

203
00:12:52,910 --> 00:12:53,790
Soon

204
00:12:53,790 --> 00:12:55,030
she might even forget me.

205
00:12:59,870 --> 00:13:01,270
Some things

206
00:13:02,670 --> 00:13:03,710
are better forgotten.

207
00:13:08,230 --> 00:13:10,190
Can I ask you for a favour?

208
00:13:11,830 --> 00:13:12,710
Go ahead.

209
00:13:13,630 --> 00:13:16,430
Can you accompany me to visit Ms Liu?

210
00:13:21,030 --> 00:13:23,150
[Yuan Yue Publishing House]

211
00:13:23,150 --> 00:13:25,080
[Count down 15 days]

212
00:13:28,750 --> 00:13:30,630
Mr Xia has gone out for a meeting today.

213
00:13:30,630 --> 00:13:32,550
I'll chair this meeting.

214
00:13:32,950 --> 00:13:33,710
Book of Luo He God

215
00:13:33,710 --> 00:13:35,870
is at the final phase.

216
00:13:36,310 --> 00:13:38,070
Chu Li,
circulation department informed that

217
00:13:38,070 --> 00:13:39,990
they lack of manpower.

218
00:13:39,990 --> 00:13:42,260
You'll have to write
the subscription letters.

219
00:13:43,190 --> 00:13:45,510
I think you should prepare
all the letters today

220
00:13:45,510 --> 00:13:47,980
along with the information sheet

221
00:13:47,980 --> 00:13:49,670
so that the circulation department
can send them out

222
00:13:49,670 --> 00:13:51,590
to the various dealers
first thing next week.

223
00:13:51,590 --> 00:13:52,430
No problem.

224
00:13:55,070 --> 00:13:57,270
I think once we obtain the first

225
00:13:57,270 --> 00:13:59,710
subscription quantity from the dealers,

226
00:14:00,110 --> 00:14:01,270
we'll know

227
00:14:01,270 --> 00:14:03,070
where this book stands

228
00:14:03,070 --> 00:14:04,670
in terms of sales potential.

229
00:14:05,430 --> 00:14:06,310
Chu Li.

230
00:14:06,430 --> 00:14:08,220
350 thousand

231
00:14:08,220 --> 00:14:09,270
is the figure you set.

232
00:14:09,430 --> 00:14:10,540
Hence,

233
00:14:10,540 --> 00:14:11,750
you have to work hard.

234
00:14:12,510 --> 00:14:13,550
[This figure]

235
00:14:13,550 --> 00:14:16,510
[is now mine to bear.]

236
00:14:16,510 --> 00:14:19,070
Mr Liang has been very supportive.

237
00:14:19,070 --> 00:14:21,790
He visited major bookstores nationwide

238
00:14:21,790 --> 00:14:24,620
to obtain a two-week placement

239
00:14:24,620 --> 00:14:27,230
at 32 Guanghua Bookstores,

240
00:14:27,700 --> 00:14:30,030
increasing the exposure
for Book of Luo He God.

241
00:14:30,030 --> 00:14:31,310
Guanghua Bookstore?

242
00:14:31,310 --> 00:14:32,670
Two-week placement?

243
00:14:32,980 --> 00:14:34,190
That's great.

244
00:14:35,470 --> 00:14:36,230
Chu Li.

245
00:14:36,590 --> 00:14:38,110
Don't get too excited just yet.

246
00:14:38,110 --> 00:14:40,670
Yuan Yue Publishing House may seem to be

247
00:14:40,670 --> 00:14:43,030
scrambling high and low

248
00:14:43,030 --> 00:14:44,710
to achieve the 350 thousand mark

249
00:14:44,710 --> 00:14:46,030
that you set

250
00:14:46,030 --> 00:14:47,350
for your book.

251
00:14:47,500 --> 00:14:48,380
However,

252
00:14:48,380 --> 00:14:49,870
you're still a rookie

253
00:14:49,870 --> 00:14:51,190
who's too young

254
00:14:51,190 --> 00:14:52,430
and lack experience.

255
00:14:52,430 --> 00:14:55,510
350 thousand is an astronomical figure.

256
00:14:55,510 --> 00:14:56,750
I think

257
00:14:56,750 --> 00:14:58,110
it's not possible at all.

258
00:15:00,430 --> 00:15:02,390
Well...

259
00:15:02,390 --> 00:15:03,990
Chu Li is a newcomer.

260
00:15:03,990 --> 00:15:06,070
Not only her,

261
00:15:06,070 --> 00:15:07,150
Deputy Editor Miao,

262
00:15:07,150 --> 00:15:08,870
even you can't achieve this figure too.

263
00:15:10,790 --> 00:15:13,230
But having said that,

264
00:15:13,230 --> 00:15:16,100
with the support we get from
marketing and circulation departments,

265
00:15:16,100 --> 00:15:17,030
who knows

266
00:15:17,030 --> 00:15:18,510
we can really achieve it.

267
00:15:18,510 --> 00:15:20,180
If a newcomer like Chu Li

268
00:15:20,180 --> 00:15:21,110
really achieve it,

269
00:15:21,110 --> 00:15:22,910
won't it be a slap in your face,
Deputy Editor Miao?

270
00:15:23,830 --> 00:15:24,550
Fine.

271
00:15:24,670 --> 00:15:26,550
I'm not afraid then.

272
00:15:26,750 --> 00:15:28,750
If this book can really

273
00:15:28,750 --> 00:15:30,710
hit that figure,

274
00:15:30,710 --> 00:15:33,070
I'll give her my title.

275
00:15:33,910 --> 00:15:34,750
Really?

276
00:15:34,950 --> 00:15:36,950
Alright then.
We'll work hard towards this.

277
00:15:38,310 --> 00:15:39,270
Alright.

278
00:15:48,630 --> 00:15:50,630
You're right on time, Mr Zhou Chuan.

279
00:15:50,630 --> 00:15:51,790
I'm preparing the subscription letter

280
00:15:51,790 --> 00:15:53,950
for your Book of Luo He God.

281
00:15:53,950 --> 00:15:55,670
The publicity wordings used in the letter

282
00:15:55,670 --> 00:15:57,990
may be used for the blurb
on the belly band later.

283
00:15:57,990 --> 00:15:58,580
Come over.

284
00:15:58,580 --> 00:16:00,270
